    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="918"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d918">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.248/8–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 3, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>232. Reference is made to message of July 31 from War Dept no. 42558 to Giles at
                        Cairo.<note n="84" xml:id="d918fn84">Not printed.</note> It is desired to
                    obtain, in connection with ATC operations in Saudi Arabia, rights permitting
                        (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) free transit of aircraft, the landing at
                    designated bases, and the transporting of personnel, matériel and mail, (<hi
                        rend="italic">b</hi>) landing in emergency at any airfield, (<hi
                        rend="italic">c</hi>) authority to station necessary personnel at designated
                    bases to provide for housekeeping, security and all necessary operations,
                    including overland supply, (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>) installation and operation
                    of weather and communications services and equipment, air navigational aids and
                    servicing facilities as may be required for all necessary operations, (<hi
                        rend="italic">e</hi>) use and security of necessary codes, and (<hi
                        rend="italic">f</hi>) carrying of traffic in the national interest as
                    provided for in Executive Order No. 9492 of Oct. 24, 1944.<note n="85"
                        xml:id="d918fn85">9 <hi rend="italic">Federal Register</hi> 12859.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Please consult Giles and endeavor to have provision for such rights included in
                    contract. These rights are desired for duration of war and an additional period
                    of three years. Advise Dept as to progress. Repeated to Cairo as Depts 1502.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
